apply

public BooleanMatrix1D apply(DoubleMatrix2D data,
                             int dataType)
                      throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
Applies the condition, returning a 1D matrix of boolean values whose elements indicate which rows should be used, where true indicates a row should be used. The input data may contain either observed data (i.e. two columns, with valid time and observations), forecasts (valid time, lead time, and members) or paired data (valid time, lead time, observations and members). The data type must be either Condition.FORECAST_DATA or Condition.PAIRED_DATA.

Specified by:
apply in class Condition
Parameters:
data - the data
dataType - the data type
Returns:
the rows that should be used given the condition
Throws:
java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
